Weird spot. Moved to the neighborhood and tried this place twice. First time ordered a chicken shawarma that was pretty bad. Dry, sketchy meat. Figured I might have had bad luck. Went back again because I was in the mood for some hummus. Ordered a large hummus (7.50) and it didn't come with any pita. Asked for pita, they gave me one piece. Asked if I could have extra, they said the one piece "was a gift". I enthusiastically offered to pay extra for extra pita, and they refused. So whatever happened there, I don't know. Never had this experience buying hummus, and I've bought a lot of hummus. Were they running low on pita? Never sold hummus before? Unfortunately, this place is not worth figuring out.
